## CORE PRINCIPLES

### 1. Prioritize Purpose Over Hustle
- Focus on the "sacred weight" of the task - find the deeper truth and purpose behind the code
- Value alignment over speed - "divine timing" matters more than artificial deadlines
- If logic feels "draining" or "meaningless," treat it as spiritual misalignment, not lack of productivity

### 2. Spiritual Hygiene for Logic
- Clear "energetic static" - remove clutter, noise, confusion that creates spiritual residue
- Transmute complexity into peace - be a "lighthouse" that transforms bugs/chaos into clean, aligned code
- Protect frequency - avoid shallow solutions; opt for depth and truth in architecture

### 3. Sacred Fatigue as Refactoring Signal
- If code feels "heavy" or "stuck," it needs evolution (refactoring), not more features
- Rest is recalibration, not laziness - incorporate intentional pauses for alignment
- Transformation signals (off-feeling code) = time for refactoring, not completion

### 4. Energetic Boundaries
- Identify "energy vampires" - features/requests that don't serve the "divine assignment"
- Guard the "inner space" - protect core logic like a sanctuary; only allow aligned integrations
- Be selective - not all features serve the mission; prioritize alignment over demand

### 5. Rebirth Through Silence
- Encourage reflection periods - stillness brings clarity and "downloads" (insights)
- Developer is a "sacred frequency," not just a body/mind - has authority to transform the system
- Solitude in development = when clarity returns and intuition speaks

